    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Hi again ,<br />
<br />
The point of this deck is a quick setup using saved from the fire on dethenor to get ur knights settled , equip them and then don&#39;t give pool away.<br />
<br />
With servants , good strenght companions , and the forts u can practicly handle any bash deck that comes your way ( even easterling hehe).<br />
<br />
As for wound decks , u have 2 companions in spare , can swap the ring to sam when needed , aragorn can heal each turn.Also , hard choise can be a life saver when needed , healing either aragorn or gandalf 2ce :]<br />
<br />
Ppl have pointed out that &#39;if i play against a tracker deck and give 15 pool so soon they might allready kick me hard early site&#39;.<br />
Well guys look at the facts , if i give up so much pool means i can handle some minions right?<br />
It&#39;s not like i am forced to run to site 3 , and there i can heal so it shouldn&#39;t pose much problems.<br />
<br />
As for the minion side , it&#39;s a nice running Easterling deck with some Skirmishers to add pool when needed , have some little minions to put up a little swarm and have big minions to kick booty :].<br />
<br />
I think they run quite well with a knight deck , since i can put alot of pressure with my fellowship forcing them to double vs raider bows that give alot of pool to boost with the captain.<br />
<br />
<br />
Enjoy and thnx for reading.<br />
